# Pre-seeded open cases — small, deliberately versioned so demos work
# out of the box. Rebuild with `python scripts/build_seed_cases.py`.
!data/seed_cases.db
# Pre-seeded simulation transactions (new dataset, 290 rows from
# lib/new_seeder.py). Tracked so a fresh clone can start the sim
# without running seed_databases.py. Regenerate with
# `python seed_databases.py`. The fired flag is reset on every API
# boot (lib/database.reset_simulation_db) so running a sim does not
# leave a persistent diff against the committed baseline.
!data/simulation.db
# Historical closed cases (IE) — curated past-investigation reference
# data. Regenerate with `python -m lib.historical_seeder` or
# `python seed_databases.py`. Tracked so fresh clones have a
# "Previous cases" panel populated out of the box.
!data/historical_cases.db
